leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT4.D3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="division" searchtype="LEGISLATION DIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="DIVISION 3 APPEARANCE [r 23]">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="DIV-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT4.D3" type="ext"/>DIVISION 3</designum></desig><title searchtype="DIV-TITLE">APPEARANCE [r 23]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,340] r 23 Appearance">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23" type="ext"/>[255,340]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Appearance</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>23</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>In a proceeding commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>, the time within which an appearance by a party to the proceeding must be filed is 21 days after service of the initiating process on the party.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An appearance must be in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F9" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 9</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A copy of the appearance must be served on the other parties to the proceeding of whose address for service the party has notice.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (3)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R23.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255340-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,340.5] Who may appear">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [255,340.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(CTH) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005X" refpt="CTH_REG_1988-269" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Admiralty Rules 1988</remotelink> r 10.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255340-5" type="ext"/>[255,340.5] </edpnum><title>Who may appear</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>In general any person who has a proprietary interest in the ship may enter an appearance and become a defendant. Eligible parties include a mortgagee, a trustee in bankruptcy, a charterer, the holder of a possessory lien or competing maritime lien or a plaintiff in another action against the same ship: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1976"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000074" spanref="cr000074-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CLR"/><ci:volume num="136"/><ci:page num="529"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000074" spanref="cr000074-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="538" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000075" spanref="cr000075-003"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="11"/><ci:page num="227"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Caltex Oil (Aust) Pty Ltd v The Dredge Willemstad</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000074-001" status="unval">(1976) 136 CLR 529</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000074-002" status="unval">at 538</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000075-003">11 ALR 227</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="90" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> (captain of the ship not permitted to intervene since he or she did not have a proprietary interest in the ship). However, even if a person has a proprietary interest in a ship, he or she may be refused leave to appear in the proceedings if he or she does not dispute the plaintiff's claim and could adequately protect his or her interest by a caveat against release of the sale proceeds under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT2.R10" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">r 10</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1909"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000076" spanref="cr000076-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WNNSW"/><ci:volume num="26"/><ci:page num="32"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Brown v Solgram</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000076-001" status="unval">(1909) 26 WN (NSW) 32</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>. A claimant competing with the plaintiff for the security represented by the ship cannot ordinarily appear to oppose an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000077" spanref="cr000077-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="SALR"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1907"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="48"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000077" spanref="cr000077-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="51" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Owners of the Ship Norma v The Ship Ardencraig</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000077-001" status="unval">[1907] SALR 48</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000077-002" status="unval">at 51&#x2013;2</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="115766" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>. It may be that a person who has no interest in the ship, but who suffers serious hardship, difficulty or danger as a result of the arrest, may be allowed to appear in the exercise of the court's inherent jurisdiction: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000078" spanref="cr000078-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1975"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="147"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">The Mardina Merchant</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000078-001" status="unval">[1975] 1 WLR 147</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> (harbour authority permitted to intervene where the presence of the arrested ship was extremely harmful to the commerce of its port). An unauthorised appearance by a person who has no right to appear does not make him or her a proper defendant: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1976"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000079" spanref="cr000079-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CLR"/><ci:volume num="136"/><ci:page num="529"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000080" spanref="cr000080-002"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="11"/><ci:page num="227"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Caltex Oil (Aust) Pty Ltd v The Dredge Willemstad</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000079-001" status="unval">(1976) 136 CLR 529</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000080-002">11 ALR 227</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="90" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255340-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,340.10] Effect of entry of appearances">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [255,340.10] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(CTH) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005X" refpt="CTH_ACT_1988-34" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Admiralty Act 1988</remotelink> Admiralty Act 1988 (Cth) s 31(1).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255340-10" type="ext"/>[255,340.10] </edpnum><title>Effect of entry of appearances</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>After appearances have been entered, the action proceeds as if it were an action <emph typestyle="it">in personam</emph> although it does not cease to be an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1976"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000081" spanref="cr000081-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="CLR"/><ci:volume num="136"/><ci:page num="529"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000081" spanref="cr000081-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="538" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000082" spanref="cr000082-003"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="11"/><ci:page num="227"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Caltex Oil (Aust) Pty Ltd v The Dredge Willemstad</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000081-001" status="unval">(1976) 136 CLR 529</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000081-002" status="unval">at 538</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000082-003">11 ALR 227</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="90" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000083" spanref="cr000083-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="AC"/><ci:volume num="2"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1983"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="450"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">The August 8</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000083-001" status="unval">[1983] 2 AC 450</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> (summary judgment awarded in an action commenced <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>). For the personal liability of a defendant if a judgment for the plaintiff is given in an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>, see the 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADA88.S31.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Admiralty Act 1988 (Cth) s 31(1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255340-15" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,340.15] Action incorrectly commenced"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255340-15" type="ext"/>[255,340.15] </edpnum><title>Action incorrectly commenced</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>If an action is incorrectly commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>, unconditional appearances by the personal defendants cannot validate it: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1977"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000084" spanref="cr000084-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="SASR"/><ci:volume num="19"/><ci:page num="112"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000084" spanref="cr000084-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="116" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Kali Boat Building and Repair Pty Ltd v Bosna</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000084-001" status="unval">(1977) 19 SASR 112</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000084-002" status="unval">at 116&#x2013;17</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="106096" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite></text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
